{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfb99-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3109"},"text":"§ 3109.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Employment of experts and consultants; temporary or intermittent","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfb9a-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" For the purpose of this section—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfb9b-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “agency” has the meaning given it by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5721"},"text":"section 5721 of this title","children":[],"tail":"; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfb9c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “appropriation” includes funds made available by statute under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s9104"},"text":"section 9104 of title 31","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfb9d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" When authorized by an appropriation or other statute, the head of an agency may procure by contract the temporary (not in excess of 1 year) or intermittent services of experts or consultants or an organization thereof, including stenographic reporting services. Services procured under this section are without regard to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfb9e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the provisions of this title governing appointment in the competitive service;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfb9f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" chapter 51 and subchapter III of chapter 53 of this title; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" section 6101(b) to (d) of title 41, except in the case of stenographic reporting services by an organization.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"However, an agency subject to chapter 51 and subchapter III of chapter 53 of this title may pay a rate for services under this section in excess of the daily equivalent of the highest rate payable under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5332"},"text":"section 5332 of this title","children":[],"tail":" only when specifically authorized by the appropriation or other statute authorizing the procurement of the services."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Positions in the Senior Executive Service or the Federal Bureau of Investigation and Drug Enforcement Administration Senior Executive Service may not be filled under the authority of subsection (b) of this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba2-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Office of Personnel Management shall prescribe regulations necessary for the administration of this section. Such regulations shall include—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba3-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" criteria governing the circumstances in which it is appropriate to employ an expert or consultant under the provisions of this section;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba4-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" criteria for setting the pay of experts and consultants under this section; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provisions to ensure compliance with such regulations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba6-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Each agency shall report to the Office of Personnel Management on an annual basis with respect to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba7-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the number of days each expert or consultant employed by the agency during the period was so employed; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba8-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s3109/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the total amount paid by the agency to each expert and consultant for such work during the period.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb7fcfba9-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/416"},"text":"80 Stat. 416","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454/tIV/s402/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454, title IV, § 402(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1160"},"text":"92 Stat. 1160","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258/s3/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258, § 3(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1063"},"text":"96 Stat. 1063","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/325/s2/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–325, § 2(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-05-30"},"text":"May 30, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/581"},"text":"102 Stat. 581","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/378/s2/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–378, § 2(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-02"},"text":"Oct. 2, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/1347"},"text":"106 Stat. 1347","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3841"},"text":"124 Stat. 3841","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb7fcfbaa-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb7fcfbab-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idb7fcfbac-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Derivation","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"U.S. Code","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised Statutes and","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Statutes at Large","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s55a"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 55a","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch744/s15"},"text":"Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 744, § 15","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/810"},"text":"60 Stat. 810","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the definitions of “agency” and “appropriation” are added on authority of the ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch744/s18"},"text":"Act of Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 744, § 18","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/811"},"text":"60 Stat. 811","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “the provisions of this title governing appointment in the competitive service” are substituted for “the civil-service laws”. The words “chapter 51 and subchapter III of chapter 53 of this title” are substituted for the reference to the classification laws which originally meant the Classification Act of 1923, as amended. Exception from the Classification Act of 1949 is based on sections 202(27) and 1106(a) of the ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-28/ch782"},"text":"Act of Oct. 28, 1949, ch. 782","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/956"},"text":"63 Stat. 956","children":[],"tail":", 972."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Standard changes are made to conform with the definitions applicable and the style of this title as outlined in the preface to the report.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb7fcfbad-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb7fcfbae-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (b)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 6101(b) to (d) of title 41” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s5"},"text":"section 5 of title 41","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsecs. (d), (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/378"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–378","children":[],"tail":" added subsecs. (d) and (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/325"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–325","children":[],"tail":" inserted reference to Federal Bureau of Investigation and Drug Enforcement Administration Senior Executive Service."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 9104” for “section 849”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb7fcfbaf-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb7fcfbb0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1978 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454","children":[],"tail":" effective 9 months after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","children":[],"tail":", and congressional review of provisions of sections 401 through 412 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454/s415"},"text":"section 415 of Pub. L. 95–454","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3131"},"text":"section 3131 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb7fcfbb1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation on Consulting Services","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/76/dG/tIV/s401"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–76, div. G, title IV, § 401","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-17"},"text":"Jan. 17, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/337"},"text":"128 Stat. 337","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/113/76/dG/tIV/s401"},"text":"“In fiscal year 2014 and thereafter, the expenditure of any appropriation under this Act [div. G of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/76"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–76","children":[],"tail":", see Tables for classification] or any subsequent Act appropriating funds for departments and agencies funded in this Act, for any consulting service through procurement contract, pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3109"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 3109","children":[],"tail":", shall be limited to those contracts where such expenditures are a matter of public record and available for public inspection, except where otherwise provided under existing law, or under existing Executive order issued pursuant to existing law.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb7fcfbb2-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Appropriations Relating to Labor, Health and Human Services, and Education; Public Disclosure of Consulting Service Through Procurement Contract","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/394/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–394, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/1825"},"text":"106 Stat. 1825","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/102/394/tV/s501"},"text":"“The expenditure of any appropriation under this Act or subsequent Departments of Labor, Health and Human Services, and Education, and Related Agencies Appropriations Acts for any consulting service through procurement contract, pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3109"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 3109","children":[],"tail":", shall be limited to those contracts where such expenditures are a matter of public record and available for public inspection, except where otherwise provided under existing law, or under existing Executive order issued pursuant to existing law.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in the following prior appropriation acts:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/170/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–170, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-11-26"},"text":"Nov. 26, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1140"},"text":"105 Stat. 1140","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/517/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–517, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/2220"},"text":"104 